The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques to generate virtual images of stained tissue samples. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of unsupervised deep learning approaches such as CycleGAN suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the validation of the approach by comparing the results of tissue analysis algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
